your computer, to help analyze how users use the website. The information generated by the cookie about your use of this website is usually transferred to a Google server in the U.S. and stored there.</p>\n\n<p>In the case of activation of IP anonymization on this website, your IP address will be stored in the Member States of the European Union or other parties under the Agreement on the European Economic Area. Only in exceptional cases may the full IP address be given to be transferred to a Google server in the U.S. Anonymization of your IP is active on this website. Google will use this information to evaluate the use of the website, compile reports on website activity and thus provide other services related to website activity and Internet on our website.</p>\n\n<p>Within the scope of Google Analytics and through its IP address, it is not associated with any other external data that Google does not have. You can refuse the use of cookies by selecting the appropriate settings on your browser. However, we point out that you may not "optionally" use the site to its full extent. You can also prevent the data generated by the cookie about your use of our site from being processed by Google (including your IP address) by downloading the following plugin.<br>\nTo download and install it visit: http://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=de.</p>\n\n<p>Realized under: <a href="https://rechtsanwalt-schwenke.de">rechtsanwalt-schwenke.de</a></p>
